  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "DMT also accepts cards instead of cash",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Motor Transport Commissioner (Development) D. said that from today (05) clients of the Motor Transport Department can use all electronic cards including credit cards to make their payments. Ms. Trofi de Silva says.",
        "The Commissioner said this while attending a news conference held at the Government News Department Auditorium today (05) to inform the public about facilitating the payment of all cash payments to the Motor Transport Department through electronic cards.",
        "Due to the adoption of new technology by the modern youth and the inconvenience of carrying money, payments are now accepted using technology. You can pay by cards even if you don't have cash on hand while getting the service.",
        "As a major agency that generates revenue for the treasury, the Department of Motor Transport gives about Rs.1 billion monthly. Due to the covid epidemic situation and decrease in vehicle imports, the income has decreased recently, but now it is recovering.",
        "Motor Transport Commissioner (Control) Mr. Susantha Jayathilaka, Accountant Mr. Aravinda Samarakoon and a group of people participated in this event."
      ],
